Description: Large marl pottery jar with high shoulder, tapering to rounded base, with a low neck and rolled rim; motifs including an ostrich (?) were incised on the shoulder after firing.
Curator's comments: Like Late ware L44k in Petrie’s Corpus of Prehistoric Pottery. Incised motifs are published in Petrie Diospolis Parva (1901), pl. XX. 33 Double falcon motif in potmark discussed in Hendrickx, et al. Early Falcons in L. Morenz and R. Kuhn (eds). Vorspann oder formative Phase? (Philippika 48) 2011, p.147
